The independent review entity shall provide to the covered person, treating provider, insurer, and the department a decision which shall include:
The findings for either the insurer or covered person regarding each issue under review;
The proposed service, treatment, drug, device, or supply for which the review was performed;
The relevant provisions in the insurer's health benefit plan and how applied; and
The relevant provisions of any nationally recognized and peer-reviewed medical or scientific documents used in the external review.
